pageContext.claim: “They [China] have a virus that started, and when it got out of control, perhaps -- I assume that's what happened; it got out of control, whichever way -- and they stopped it from going to China, but they didn't stop it from going to the rest of the world.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump makes it appear as China did not suffer from the outbreak of the coronavirus in Wuhan province. At least 5,000 people died and the number is probably much higher than that. The Chinese government was slow to react at first but then took dramatic steps -- such as shutting down Wuhan -- that limited the spread within China.
